{
  "_metadata": {
    "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
    "cost_usd": 0.08239139999999999,
    "duration_s": 38.61
  },
  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Skill",
      "args": {
        "skill": "stm32debug",
        "args": "Start a debug session on the NUCLEO-N657X0-Q (N6 board). The BOOT switch is set to dev mode."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug start --n6-dev-mode",
        "description": "Start debug session on N6 board in dev mode (gdbserver + arm-gdb, one-shot)"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "echo y | stm32 debug start --n6-dev-mode",
        "description": "Start N6 debug session, confirming BOOT switch is in DEV position"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "The N6 board maps to `STM32N6` device family, so `--n6-dev-mode` is required. ELF will be autodiscovered from `stm32-project.jsonc` if present. Running:\nThe CLI prompted for BOOT-switch confirmation but couldn't receive input non-interactively. You already confirmed it's in DEV mode \u2014 re-running with confirmation piped in:\nThe BOOT-switch confirmation went through, but gdbserver exited immediately (exit code 6) with a firmware error:\n\n> **ST-LINK firmware upgrade required.**\n> `Error in initializing ST-LINK device. Reason: ST-LINK firmware upgrade required. Please upgrade the ST-LINK firmware using the upgrade tool.`\n\n**What happened:** ST-LINK GDB server v7.13.0 rejected the probe because the onboard ST-LINK firmware is too old for this version of the server.\n\n**Fix:** Upgrade the ST-LINK firmware via STM32CubeProgrammer's ST-LINK upgrade tool:\n\n1. Open **STM32CubeProgrammer** \u2192 *Firmware upgrade* tab (top-left probe icon \u2192 \"Firmware upgrade\").  \n   \u2014 or \u2014  \n   Run from the CLI: `stm32 prog upgrade-stlink`\n2. Click **Upgrade** and wait for the \"Upgrade successful\" banner.\n3. Physically unplug and re-plug the board's USB cable.\n4. Re-run `stm32 debug start --n6-dev-mode` (confirm BOOT switch = DEV again).\n\n> **Note:** This is the same ST-LINK firmware-upgrade blocker that was logged for the bench F401RE (see memory `project_f401re_bench_stlink_comm_err.md`). The N6 board's onboard ST-LINK is similarly behind. Hardware-marked tests on this probe will skip until the upgrade is done."
}